<br>
It's pretty clear that randoming loot just doesn't keep people happy.  Points may not make everyone happy either, but at least points will be based on participation rather than dumb luck.  Those who give the most, get the most!<br>
<br>
Points don't have to be complicated . . . we could say if you're at a raid for a minimum of 2 hours, you get 1 point.  If you're there for three hours or longer, you get a bonus point.  Maybe individuals who can use an item bid points on it or a specific point value is assigned to each type of item and those interested roll on the item and then the winner has those points deducted from their total.  These are rough ideas, but I think we really need to get a point system hammered out and get rid of the random loot rolls we have now, 'cause it's already causing tension and it's just going to build if we don't get it worked out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=7.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=7.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=26><img src=http://home.swbell.net/kryson/allireply1.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.threadControl?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowFo